From: Sergey Miroshnichenko <neg-serg@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH] daemon: fix double-free in Output::destroy on shutdown

When the daemon is stopped while a wallpaper transition is in flight,
`Output::destroy` would free `transition.new_texture` and then free
`wallpaper.texture`, which share the same underlying vk::Image /
vk::ImageView / vk::DeviceMemory handles (see the transition-completion
path around main.rs:1094 and the early-destroy guard at main.rs:1181).

The double free was caught by glibc malloc during the teardown of
radv's internal bookkeeping, aborting the process with SIGABRT from
within DaemonState::destroy_all.

Fix: do not destroy `transition.new_texture` in Output::destroy — its
handles are already owned by `self.wallpaper.texture` and will be
freed via that path.
---
 daemon/src/output.rs | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/daemon/src/output.rs
+++ b/daemon/src/output.rs
@@ -195,7 +195,13 @@
         unsafe {
             if let Some(transition) = self.transition.take() {
                 transition.old_texture.destroy(device);
-                transition.new_texture.destroy(device);
+                // NOTE: do NOT destroy transition.new_texture — its Vulkan
+                // handles are shared with self.wallpaper.texture (see the
+                // transition-completion path in main.rs around line 1094
+                // and the early-destroy guard at line 1181). Freeing both
+                // would cause a double-free in the radv allocator and
+                // glibc-malloc would abort the process (SIGABRT in
+                // DaemonState::destroy_all on shutdown).
             }
             if let Some(animation) = self.animation.take() {
                 animation.atlas.destroy(device);
